dcterms:description: A novel tool that simulates infection spread and facilitates the exploration of various reinforcement learning algorithms in response to epidemic challenges, specifically designed for educational settings.
dcterms:title: SafeCampus

dcterms:description: A compartmental model used to simulate the spread of infectious diseases, focusing on the dynamics of susceptible, exposed, infected, and recovered individuals.
dcterms:title: SEIR Model

dcterms:description: A compartmental model used to simulate the spread of infectious diseases, focusing on the dynamics of susceptible, infected, and recovered individuals.
dcterms:title: SIR Model

dcterms:description: A compartmental model that includes susceptible, infected, hospitalized, and recovered individuals, used to simulate the dynamics of infectious diseases.
dcterms:title: SIHR Model

dcterms:description: A model that represents the dynamics of disease spread across multiple populations or locations, often used in epidemic modeling.
dcterms:title: Meta-population Model

dcterms:description: A modeling approach that simulates the actions and interactions of autonomous agents to assess their effects on the system as a whole, particularly in the context of epidemic spread.
dcterms:title: Agent-based Model

dcterms:description: General reference to data related to the COVID-19 pandemic, used for modeling and analysis in various studies.
dcterms:title: COVID-19 Data
